(8) Unusual mortalities: Seal predation affects CN and PK runs. Riverine seals hunting right up to fence. (14) Flood: March 1997 flood adversely affects all Area 14 streams. Oct. 10 flood destroys 1/3 of fence and renders it ineffective for about a week until temporary patch could be put in place. (20) On Salmon Distribution or Predator Interactions: Excessive seal predation continues to have effects on chinook and pinks due to low levels for returns. Seal cull commenced this year. 39 animals shot. Continuation of cull is uncertain. Low abundance of pinks made it difficult for anglers and harvest appears to have been negligible by the local sport fleet.
